{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To examine the ability of AI to write convincing, undetectable academic writing, Gao et al. (2022) prompted ChatGPT-3 to write 50 research abstracts based on 50 published abstracts in medical journals.",
    "These researchers then analyzed these abstracts using a plagiarism detector, and four human reviewers for originality.",
    "The plagiarism detector revealed 100% originality suggesting the writing was original.",
    "The human reviewers, who were each given 25 abstracts that were a mixture of AI and human generated (i.e., the original abstracts), correctly identified 68% of ChatGPT-3 generated abstracts and incorrectly identified 14% of the original abstracts as being AI generated.",
    "Gao and colleagues also used the GPT-2 Output Detector to detect whether abstracts were generated by AI."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To examine the ability of AI to write convincing, undetectable academic writing, Gao et al. (2022) prompted ChatGPT-3 to write 50 research abstracts based on 50 published abstracts in medical journals."
  ]
}